,\\n      \\\"version\\\" : \\\"3\\\"\\n    },\\n    \\\"tested-versions\\\" : [\\n      \\\"1.3.0\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"allowed-packages\\\" : [\\n      \\\"org.apache.pekko.http.ccompat\\\",\\n      \\\"org.apache.pekko.macros\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n]\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778136885271}]}\n2241:[thinking] **Exploring functional coverage**\n2243:[thinking] I need to think about functional coverage, which might involve class/object and macro-generated elements. It also seems important to consider testing and debug levels like info or warning. Since I can't access a particular trait, I wonder if creating a helper in the org.apache.pekko package would be possible, but there's a rule against using the same package. I might explore Java implementation, though tests in Scala under a different package could still extend a Java-public interface.\n2249:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Exploring functional coverage**\\n\\nI need to think about functional coverage, which might involve class/object and macro-generated elements. It also seems important to consider testing and debug levels like info or warning. Since I can't access a particular trait, I wonder if creating a helper in the org.apache.pekko package would be possible, but there's a rule against using the same package. I might explore Java implementation, though tests in Scala under a different package could still extend a Java-public interface.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_099444905eef4ef20169fc373fcd888190873098042b6cd52b\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_DdNpUhQEG72iIFMtfKOmLjYRYjp0pvz9lR52sFDFAUryzHREnPldA5330y4W2raEhE6d3HOkYKYzO2UL3_6VZmlTM5EQ6JyCSPVGezXs0EeeCY1ZTQG-HcqvYXNaEkGs40rB2PG8Eo5SX_OmPOyuATgWIOX9OTHsLDTB3SC35W_f2KI2OUbbxrMjra3XcbXuqyf0H2QQT5nQTnVc7f02JmL6-WmWvrdpve6a_k3r9Z6jrsSaloi1Kn_Vq6k9MBLBO8d-RSBCcPiI1OutmhbdwBlCcJ-fjsCBBszP